<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-08-13T23:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-08-13T23:00:00-05:00" n="463" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d463">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/9374: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-08-14T12:00:00+08:00">August 14, 1937—noon [<hi rend="italic">midnight</hi>].</date><lb/>[Received
                                    August 15—11:40 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>435. My 433, August 14, 10 p.m., British Ambassador has just informed
                                me that Minister for Foreign Affairs called on him this evening and
                                stated that Generalissimo expressed interest in formula <pb facs="0422" n="415" xml:id="pg_415"/> presented by Consuls at
                                Shanghai (see Shanghai’s 473 of August 13, 9 p.m.<note n="14" xml:id="d463fn14"><ref target="frus1931-41v01#pg_346"><hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, Japan, 1931–1941,
                                        vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 346</ref>.</note>) but
                                wanted to know what guarantee he had that Japanese would carry out
                                and keep such an agreement. British Ambassador suggested that he
                                should discuss this with Japanese and renewed offer of neutral
                                observers to watch carrying out of any agreement for mutual
                                withdrawal two countries might reach.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>